<accesscontrol>审核人:遗传模式,审核人:所有成员(ro),编辑人:普通用户(ro)</accesscontrol>
=遗传模式(27条目)=


==[[HP:0000005]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0000005
| 名称 = Mode of inheritance
| 定义 = The pattern in which a particular genetic trait or disorder is passed from one generation to the next.
| 中文译名 = 遗传模式
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


==[[HP:0000006]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0000006
| 名称 = Autosomal dominant inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in heterozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, an autosomal dominant disorder is caused when a single copy of the mutant allele is present. Males and females are affected equally, and can both transmit the disorder with a risk of 50% for each child of inheriting the mutant allele.
| 中文译名 = 常染色体显性遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


==[[HP:0000007]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0000007
| 名称 = Autosomal recessive inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in homozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, autosomal recessive disorders manifest in homozygotes (with two copies of the mutant allele) or compound heterozygotes (whereby each copy of a gene has a distinct mutant allele).
| 中文译名 = 常染色体隐性遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}

==[[HP:0001417]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001417
| 名称 = X-linked inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome.
| 中文译名 = X-连锁遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}

==[[HP:0001419]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001419
| 名称 = X-linked recessive inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for recessive traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome. In the context of medical genetics, X-linked recessive disorders manifest in males (who have one copy of the X chromosome and are thus hemizygotes), but generally not in female heterozygotes who have one mutant and one normal allele.
| 中文译名 = X-连锁隐性遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}

==[[HP:0001423]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001423
| 名称 = X-linked dominant inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for dominant traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome. In the context of medical genetics, X-linked dominant disorders tend to manifest very severely in affected males. The severity of manifestation in females may depend on the degree of skewed X inactivation.
| 中文译名 = X-连锁显性遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}

==[[HP:0001425]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001425
| 名称 = Heterogeneous
| 定义 = #####
| 中文译名 = 异质性的
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


==[[HP:0001426]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001426
| 名称 = Multifactorial inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that depends on a mixture of major and minor genetic determinants possibly together with environmental factors. Diseases inherited in this manner are termed complex diseases.
| 中文译名 = 多因素遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}

==[[HP:0001427]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001427
| 名称 = Mitochondrial inheritance
| 定义 = A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on the mitochondrial genome. Because the mitochondrial genome is essentially always maternally inherited, a mitochondrial condition can only be transmitted by females, although the condition can affect both sexes. The proportion of mutant mitochondria can vary (heteroplasmy).
| 中文译名 = 线粒体遗传
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


==[[HP:0001428]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001428
| 名称 = Somatic mutation
| 定义 = #####
| 中文译名 = 体细胞突变
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


==[[HP:0001442]]==
{{Infobox HPO
| hpoId = HP:0001442
| 名称 = Somatic mosaicism
| 定义 = The presence of genetically distinct populations of somatic cells in a given organism caused by DNA mutations, epigenetic alterations of DNA, chromosomal abnormalities or the spontaneous reversion of inherited mutations.
| 中文译名 = 体细胞嵌合体
| 中文定义 = #####
}}


